snippet: Alice McKennis won a World Cup women’s downhill race in Austria, while Lindsey Vonn was sixth after returning from a break.
abstract: Winter Sports Roundup; Alice McKennis wins downhill race in St Anton, Austria, for her first World Cup victory, as Lindsey Vonn, returning from a nearly monthlong break, finishes sixth; other news noted.
lead_paragraph: Alice McKennis won a World Cup women’s downhill race in Austria, while Lindsey Vonn was sixth after returning from a break.

headline.seo: In Downhill, McKennis of the U.S. Parlays Early Run Into First World Cup Victory
headline.main: McKennis of U.S. Gains First World Cup Skiing Victory, and Ligety His 15th
headline.print_headline: McKennis of the U.S. Parlays Early Run Into Her First World Cup Victory
